                    <pb facs="0498" n="402" xml:id="pg_402"/>
                    <p>The increase in the production of silver in Germany since the year 1871, was
                        caused principally by the smelting of foreign ores (derived chiefly from the
                        western shores of America) which, however, has again decreased since the
                        year 1874. From foreign silver ores, there were produced in Germany: <table
                            cols="2" rows="7">
                            <row>
                                <cell/>
